# Files / dirs the Dockerfile does NOT need shipped into the build context.
# Everything here is either re-derived inside the image (build outputs,
# node_modules) or is irrelevant at runtime (test fixtures, IDE state,
# git history).
#
# Trim the build context aggressively: a few hundred MB of node_modules
# and .next caches sent over the docker daemon socket adds noticeable
# latency to `docker build` even with BuildKit's tar streaming.

# ─── Build outputs (rebuilt inside the image) ─────────────────────────
.next/
out/
build/
dist/
publish/

# ─── Dependencies (re-installed in the deps stage) ────────────────────
node_modules/
.pnpm-store/

# ─── Tests, fixtures, e2e (not needed in the runtime tree) ────────────
coverage/
.nyc_output/
**/__tests__/
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
__tests__/
e2e/
playwright-report/
playwright.config.ts

# ─── Tooling state ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.turbo/
.cache/
.eslintcache
*.tsbuildinfo
.entity-builder-backups/
.entity-builder-cache/

# ─── IDE / editor / OS noise ──────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
.windsurfrules
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Source control ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.github/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# ─── Secrets ─ never in an image ──────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ─── Docs / runbooks (not part of the runtime contract) ───────────────
docs/
*.md
!README.md

# ─── The Dockerfile itself + this ignore file ─────────────────────────
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# ─── Misc that shouldn't ship ─────────────────────────────────────────
.vercel/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
